cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL

The paper presents a functional, phenomenological model of the primate visual cortex that uses unsupervised learning, information compression, and feedback. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, given the focus on visual processing and the use of neural networks, cs.CV and cs.NE are the most likely categories.
